    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 11.94,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 17.44,
      "end": 22.5,
      "text": "Aesop's Fables, the Wolf, the Fox, and the Ape.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 23.56,
      "end": 29.56,
      "text": "A Wolf charged a fox with theft, which he denied, and the case was brought before an",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 29.56,
      "end": 30.6,
      "text": "ape to be tried.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 31.28,
      "end": 36.64,
      "text": "When he had heard the evidence on both sides, the ape gave judgment as follows.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 37.66,
      "end": 42.74,
      "text": "I do not think, he said, that you, a wolf, ever lost what you claim.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 43.54,
      "end": 49.34,
      "text": "But all the same, I believe that you, Fox, are guilty of the theft, in spite of all your",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 49.34,
      "end": 49.8,
      "text": "denials.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 51.32,
      "end": 55.66,
      "text": "The dishonest get no credit, even if they act honestly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 57.02,
      "end": 61.66,
      "text": "End of the Wolf, the Fox, and the Ape.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
